            <div class="hero-unit">
              <h2>Welcome to Hawley Farm Holiday Lets</h2>
              <p>... quietly situated away from the sight and sounds of the hustle and bustle of everyday life. A secluded location with birds nesting in large trees, water running in streams and wind rustling leaves ...</p>
            </div>
            <div class="row-fluid">
              <div class="span6">
		<h2>The Holiday Lets</h2>
	     	<p>Two rustic, yet modern places to stay. Log fires, oak floors and great views, yet also ensuite bathrooms, underfloor heating and free WiFi throughout. The Wagon House has 2 bedrooms and the Cider Press has 3 bedrooms.</p>
              </div><!--/span-->
              <div class="span6">
		<h2>The Farm</h2>
		<p>A mainly dairy farm, however also with sheep and beef. Come to learn about and interact with a real working farm. Find out how supermarkets get their milk, how butchers get their meat and how we all get great tasting food.</p>
              </div><!--/span-->
            </div><!--/row-->
            <div class="row-fluid">
              <div class="span6">
		<h2>The Location</h2>
		<p>We are in a designated "area of outstanding natural beauty", the Blackdown Hills, a part of East Devon. This area is a perfect place for walkers and cyclists. Nearby is the historic village of Dalwood, the world heritage site of the Jurassic Coast, Dartmoor National Park and more.</p>
              </div><!--/span-->
              <div class="span6">
		<h2>A Good Stay?</h2>
		<p>Since we started two years ago, many guests have left reviews of their stay. To predict how good your stay will be without the marketing bias of this wesite, we recommend that you take a read of them. If you have already stayed, then please add your review for the rest of the world to see.</p>
              </div><!--/span-->
            </div><!--/row-->
